comments.body:
`file.reader(header,28)` maybe read fewer than 28 bytes in the file is shorter than expected. Remaining bytes in header would be uninitialized. `std::any_of` would read them â€” which is UB.

```
file.read(header, 28);
if (file.gcount() != 28) return;
```
This bails out if we didn't get a full header, which is the safe default

